radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar dependent atelectasis; retrocecal appendix mildly dilated (8-9 mm), mild hyperemia of wall, minimal periappendiceal fat stranding; multiple subcentimeter reactive lymph nodes in right lower quadrant; no hydronephrosis, free fluid, or bowel obstruction; multiple subserosal fibroids in uterus; small amount of pelvic free fluid.
